cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

This paper is about understanding the internal work mechanism of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) by visualizing their internal representations. The paper focuses on image classification tasks, which is a common application of CNNs. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the complexity and architecture of CNNs, which suggests that it may belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper uses visualization techniques to analyze the internal representations of CNNs, which could be related to cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
